{"word":"ἀναβοάω","slug":"ἀναβοάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναβοάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>The form <el>ἀναβοάσω</el> is aor1, not future.\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to shout aloud, utter a loud cry</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; of <i>a war-cry</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to call out</i> that . . , <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to cry out</i> something, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; also <i>to wail aloud over</i> a misfortune, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to call on</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}